A Control System for Biosaxs Experiments 

Ricardo N. Fernandes, Darren P. Spruce

  • Python and Qt
  • Built using an in-house framework called Bliss FrameWork 4
  • Communication with devices is separated from UI
Features

  • Start and control a data acquisition according to user’s parameters

  • Display images being acquired from the detector apparatus

  • Post-processing of the 1D curves, such as cropping or subtracting

  • Reprocess the collected data with different parameters

  • Control of the sample changer to enable automatic batch experiments
